article.headline: Cornell 68, Dartmouth 62
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Ka'Ron Barnes scored 25 points and Cody Toppert added 22 as Cornell defeated Dartmouth, 68-62, Saturday night. The victory gave Cornell (9-8) an Ivy League record of 4-0 for the first time since the 1964-65 season. With 16 points in the first half, Barnes pushed the Big Red to a 35-29 lead at the break. Cornell held a 51-39 lead with 12:32 to play when Barnes hit one of his six 3-point baskets. Dartmouth (3-15, 1-3), which has lost eight straight, got within six points three times in the final four minutes, but couldn't get closer. Leon Pattman had 21 points and a game-high 12 rebounds for Dartmouth.
